  "name": "Torturous Trauma",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>With this spell born of Kemnebi's sadistic love of torture, you batter a creature's internal organs, leaving no external signs of the immense pain you delivered. The target takes bludgeoning damage equal to 1d4 + your spellcasting modifier with a basic Fortitude save. If it critically fails, the target is also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued} until the start of your next turn. Creatures that lack internal organs are unaffected by this spell.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The bludgeoning damage increases by 1d4.</p>"
